---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import CtaBanner from '../../components/CtaBanner.astro';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="701am — Earned Media for AI Companies"
  description="Every company now claims to be an AI company, and the noise is deafening. Earned media that separates the AI companies with a real, defensible story from the ones just riding the wave — and puts yours on the record."
  breadcrumbs={[
    { name: 'Industries', url: '/industries' },
    { name: 'AI' },
  ]}
>

  <!-- ════ HERO ════ -->
  <section class="hero" id="top">
    <div class="hero-grain" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-rays" aria-hidden="true"></div>
    <div class="hero-sun" aria-hidden="true"></div>

    <div class="hero-content">
      <p class="hero-overline">
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
        Industries · For AI companies
        <span class="hero-overline-rule"></span>
      </p>

      <h1 class="hero-headline">
        Everyone says they're AI now.<br />The press decides <em>who means it.</em>
      </h1>

      <p class="hero-deck">
        The category is the loudest in technology, and the buyer cannot tell the substance from the wrapper. <em>An earned story is the one credential a 'we use AI' claim cannot fake — it is how the market learns which AI companies are real.</em>
      </p>

      <div class="cta-cluster">
        <a class="btn-primary" href="/discovery">
          Book a sunrise call
          <span class="btn-icon" aria-hidden="true">→</span>
        </a>
        <a class="btn-link" href="#method">
          See how it works
          <span class="arrow" aria-hidden="true">↓</span>
        </a>
      </div>

      <p class="cta-fine">Thirty minutes. No deck. No pitch. No charge.</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ PRESS STRIP ════ -->
  <section class="press-strip" aria-label="Where the AI story gets told">
    <div class="press-inner">
      <p class="press-label">
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
        Where the AI story gets told
        <span class="press-star">★</span>
      </p>
      <div class="press-logos">
        <span class="press-logo press-MIT TECHNOLOGY REVIEW">condensed</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-Wired">italic</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-TECHCRUNCH">condensed</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-The Information">italic</span>
        <span class="press-logo press-VentureBeat">roman</span>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 01 — THE FIRST TRUTH ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 01 · The first truth</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">In the loudest category in tech,<br /><em>substance is the only signal.</em></h2>
      <div class="body">
        <p class="dropcap">
          Every company now claims AI: AI-powered, AI-native, AI-first. A buyer, an investor, a recruit hears the same three prefixes on every landing page, so they tune out the claim entirely and search for the one signal the wrapper cannot fake: <em>has a serious publication taken this company seriously.</em>
        </p>

        <div class="aphorism">The model is not the story — the proof is</div>

        <p>
          That credibility is not bought with a louder launch or a bigger demo budget. It is earned when a reporter who actually understands the technology writes about <strong>you</strong>, when your researcher's view runs in the publication the field respects, when your name is cited in the story instead of lost in the hype cycle.
        </p>

        <p>
          The proof is in your own work right now. The benchmark you can defend. The capability that is genuinely new. The honest limitation everyone else is hiding. Each is a story a technology reporter is hunting for — and is desperate to find amid the noise — that <em>cannot come from a company just bolting a chatbot onto its product.</em> Most AI companies pitch the hype. The real ones pitch the proof, and the press rewards them for it.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 02 — THE LEDGER ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy ledger-section">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 02 · The ledger</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What an earned placement <em>does for a desk.</em></h2>

      <div class="ledger-grid">
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">16</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Placements earned</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">In a single quarter</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">3</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Technical outlets</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">MIT Tech Review · Wired · more</div>
        </div>
        <div class="ledger-divider" aria-hidden="true"></div>
        <div class="ledger-cell">
          <div class="ledger-num">1</div>
          <div class="ledger-cap">Un-ignorable result</div>
          <div class="ledger-sub">Pulled from your own benchmarks</div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="ledger-prose">
        <p>
          The pattern repeats across AI companies. We spend the first weeks finding the result no competitor can claim — a benchmark you can defend, a capability that is genuinely first, a use case that proves it works — and the rest placing it where the serious press and your buyers read. <em>The model changes. The mechanism does not.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Illustrative of the pattern. Client specifics confidential. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 03 — THE METHOD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="method">
    <div class="container reveal">
      <p class="proclamation-hinge">
        The office holds the same two articles, whatever the industry on the masthead —
      </p>

      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 03 · The method</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2 h2-dark">Two things. Done <em>without compromise.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-dark body-center">
        <p>
          We do not write your launch thread or run your demo days. We build the conditions under which the market already takes your AI seriously before the pitch. <em>The method fits on a single page, and it does not bend for the hype cycle.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <article class="doc">
        <header class="doc-header">
          <div class="doc-stamp">★ Tenets of the office ★</div>
          <h3 class="doc-title">The Two Articles of Earned Authority</h3>
          <p class="doc-sub">Adopted at sunrise. Held for the AI desk.</p>
        </header>

        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. i</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Find the angle inside your real results.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              Buried in your benchmarks and your roadmap is one true sentence about what is genuinely new that no competitor can claim and no editor can refuse. <em>It is almost never the thing in your launch tweet.</em> We sit with your research and product teams until we find it, and then we sharpen it until it cuts.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="tenet">
          <div class="tenet-mark">Art. ii</div>
          <div>
            <h4 class="tenet-h">Place it where the field reads.</h4>
            <p class="tenet-p">
              A claim in a launch post is just more noise. We do the unglamorous work — the research, the pitch, the follow-up — until the right reporter at <em>MIT Technology Review</em> or <em>Wired</em> runs the story. Then we do it again, until your name is the one cited when the field discusses what is real.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="doc-sig">
          <p class="doc-sig-line">— 701am, est. at sunrise</p>
          <div class="doc-sig-title">Office of Earned Media</div>
        </div>
        <div class="doc-wax">7:01</div>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § 04 — THE WORK ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy" id="work">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ 04 · The work</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">Three engagements.<br /><em>Built for the desk.</em></h2>
      <div class="body body-center">
        <p>
          Three ways the office goes to work on an AI company. <em>Pick the one that fits the moment you are in.</em>
        </p>
      </div>

      <div class="stamp-rule">
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-time">7:01</div>
        <div class="stamp-rule-bar"></div>
      </div>

      <div class="eng-grid">
        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">i.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement I · The fastest</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Mine the <em>real-results story.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            We turn your benchmarks and capabilities into a single reporter-ready angle on what is genuinely new — the proof point that separates you from the hype.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Audit of your results</li>
            <li>One un-ignorable thesis</li>
            <li>Reporter-ready memo</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">ii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement II · The campaign</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Own the <em>category narrative.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            A sustained placement campaign across the technical and business press the field respects. Your founder or researcher becomes the named voice on where the technology is actually going.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Pitch · place · follow-up</li>
            <li>MIT Tech Review · Wired · TechCrunch</li>
            <li>Technical positioning</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="eng-card">
          <div class="eng-num">iii.</div>
          <div class="eng-tier">Engagement III · The engine</div>
          <h3 class="eng-h">Arm your <em>internal team.</em></h3>
          <p class="eng-p">
            The earned-media skills your comms or research lead can run themselves — pitch craft, journalist research, the angle-finder — tuned to the AI beat and built to outlast any one launch.
          </p>
          <ul class="eng-list">
            <li>Earned-media playbook</li>
            <li>AI &amp; tech press list</li>
            <li>Repeatable, in-house</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ FOUNDER NOTE ════ -->
  <section class="founder-note">
    <div class="founder-inner reveal">
      <p class="founder-eyebrow">
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
        A note from the office
        <span class="founder-rule"></span>
      </p>
      <blockquote class="founder-quote">
        There are a thousand companies claiming to be AI. There are perhaps a handful the serious press would put on the record. <em>We are built to make you one of them.</em> If you have the substance and the market can't hear it over the noise, the sunrise call is free.
      </blockquote>
      <p class="founder-sig">
        <span class="founder-name">— David</span>
        <span class="founder-time">at 7:01</span>
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ § — FROM THE FIELD ════ -->
  <section class="section section-navy">
    <div class="container-wide reveal">
      <div class="section-label">
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
        <div class="label-text">§ — From the field</div>
        <div class="label-bar"></div>
      </div>
      <h2 class="h2">What the desk <em>hears back.</em></h2>

      <div class="field-grid">
        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            They found the one benchmark in our work we could actually defend and built the whole story around it. The MIT Tech Review piece changed how investors saw us.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Co-founder</span>
            <span class="field-role">AI infrastructure company</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            Everyone in our space launches with the same hype. The earned coverage signalled we were the real one, and enterprise buyers noticed.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">CEO</span>
            <span class="field-role">Applied-AI startup</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>

        <figure class="field-card">
          <div class="field-mark" aria-hidden="true">&ldquo;</div>
          <blockquote class="field-quote">
            What I paid for was placements. What I got was credibility with a press that is rightly sceptical of AI claims. That trust compounds.
          </blockquote>
          <figcaption class="field-by">
            <span class="field-name">Head of Comms</span>
            <span class="field-role">Foundation-model company</span>
          </figcaption>
        </figure>
      </div>

      <p class="ledger-coda">★ Names withheld where confidentiality required. Words unchanged. ★</p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- ════ CTA ════ -->
  <CtaBanner
    eyebrow="The work begins at 7:01"
    heading="Ready to be the AI company <em>the press takes seriously?</em>"
    body="Thirty minutes. We listen, find the result hiding in your own benchmarks, and tell you straight whether we can put your substance on the record."
    primaryLabel="Book a sunrise call"
    primaryHref="/discovery"
    secondaryLabel="Or read the field manual"
    secondaryHref="/legend-maker"
  />

</BaseLayout>

<style>
  /* ─────── WHO THIS IS FOR — buyer-segment cards (optional) ─────── */
  .aud-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .aud-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .aud-card + .aud-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .aud-tag {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
  }
  .aud-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.1;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .aud-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .aud-p em { font-style: italic; color: var(--claret); }
  .aud-line {
    margin: 0;
    padding-top: var(--x4);
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.10em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    line-height: 1.6;
  }

  /* ─────── ENGAGEMENTS — mirrors the index "offers" three-up ─────── */
  .eng-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: 0;
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
    border: 1px solid var(--rule-strong);
    background: var(--rule-strong);
  }
  .eng-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5));
    position: relative;
  }
  .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
  .eng-num {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-weight: 300;
    font-size: var(--f3-size);
    line-height: 1;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-variant-numeric: oldstyle-nums;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-tier {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 10px;
    letter-spacing: 0.22em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-bottom: var(--x4);
  }
  .eng-h {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "dlig" 1;
    font-size: var(--f4-size);
    line-height: 1.12;
    font-weight: 500;
    color: var(--ink);
    letter-spacing: -0.018em;
    margin: 0 0 var(--x4);
    text-wrap: balance;
  }
  .eng-h em { font-style: italic; font-weight: 400; color: var(--claret); }
  .eng-p {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink-soft);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
  }
  .eng-list {
    list-style: none;
    margin: 0;
    padding: var(--x4) 0 0;
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
  }
  .eng-list li {
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 13px;
    color: var(--ink-faint);
    padding: var(--x5) 0;
    display: flex;
    align-items: baseline;
    gap: var(--x4);
    counter-increment: eng;
  }
  .eng-list { counter-reset: eng; }
  .eng-list li::before {
    content: counter(eng, lower-roman) ".";
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    color: var(--claret);
    font-size: 12px;
    min-width: 1.4em;
  }

  /* ─────── FROM THE FIELD — mirrors the index testimonial cards ─────── */
  .field-grid {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
    gap: var(--x3);
    max-width: 64rem;
    margin: var(--x1) auto 0;
  }
  .field-card {
    background: var(--paper-soft);
    border: 1px solid var(--rule);
    border-top: 3px solid var(--claret);
    padding: var(--x2) calc(var(--x2) - var(--x5)) var(--x2);
    margin: 0;
    display: flex;
    flex-direction: column;
  }
  .field-mark {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-size: 3rem;
    line-height: 0.5;
    height: 1.1rem;
    color: var(--claret);
  }
  .field-quote {
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-feature-settings: "kern" 1, "liga" 1, "onum" 1;
    font-size: var(--f6-size);
    line-height: 1.5;
    color: var(--ink);
    margin: 0 0 var(--x3);
    flex: 1;
    text-wrap: pretty;
  }
  .field-by {
    border-top: 1px solid var(--rule);
    padding-top: var(--x4);
  }
  .field-name {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Newsreader', Georgia, serif;
    font-style: italic;
    font-size: var(--f5-size);
    color: var(--claret);
    line-height: 1.2;
  }
  .field-role {
    display: block;
    font-family: 'Instrument Sans', sans-serif;
    font-size: 11px;
    letter-spacing: 0.16em;
    text-transform: uppercase;
    color: var(--ink-fainter);
    font-weight: 600;
    margin-top: var(--x5);
  }

  /* ─────── RESPONSIVE ─────── */
  @media (max-width: 860px) {
    .aud-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .aud-card + .aud-card { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
    .eng-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
    .eng-card + .eng-card { border-left: none; border-top: 1px solid var(--rule-strong); }
    .field-grid { grid-template-columns: 1fr; }
  }
</style>
